- The tempo is measured in beats per minute (BPM);
- A progression's probability indicates its likelihood of occurring in a given musical context.

- "maestro of the orchestra" refers to the user with the highest number of progressions;
- "leading the most compositions" refers to the user who has created the most progressions;
- "compositions" in this context are analogous to progressions in the database.

sql:
SELECT progression_name, progression_key
FROM progressions
WHERE progression_mode = 'Ionian' AND progression_tempo > 100;

SELECT AVG(progression_tempo) AS average_heartbeat, AVG(probability) AS average_likelihood
FROM progressions
WHERE progression_key = 'C Major';

SELECT progression_name
FROM progressions
WHERE progression_id = 1;

